title: No. 19 Georgia loses Chubb, falls 38-31 to Tennessee (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,191 No. 19 Georgia loses Chubb, falls 38-31 to Tennessee (Yahoo Sports) Joshua Dobbs threw for a career-high 312 yards, ran for 118 more and accounted for five touchdowns Saturday as Tennessee erased a 21-point deficit in a 38-31 victory over the 19th-ranked Bulldogs. The defeat was doubly painful for Georgia (4-2, 1-2 SEC), which lost star running back Nick Chubb to an injured left knee on the game's first snap. Georgia coach Mark Richt was unsure after the game about the severity of Chubb's injury.
